                                More

        More enables you to view ASCII text files on the Workbench. To view
a text file, select the More icon by clicking on it, then hold down the
Shift key and double-click on the icon of the text file you wish to view.
If the file doesn't have an icon, use the Show All Files menu item in the
Window menu to assign it a pseudo-icon.

        An alternative way to view a file is to double-click on the
More icon, which brings up a requester asking for the file you wish to
view. Scroll through the list of drawers and files and use the Pattern,
Drawer and file gadgets to specify the file. If the file is on another
disk, select the Disks gadget to show which disks are available.

        There are various commands used to more about through the text
file. The most important ones are:

        Space bar: Moves the files on by a page.

        Back-space or b: Moves the file back by a page.

        Return: Moves the file on by a line.

        <: Goes back to the first page.

        >: Goes to the last page.

        H: Shows a list of all the commands available in More.

        Q: Quits the program.

        Ctrl-C: Quits the program.

        More also enables you to search for a string of text in the
document. Typing/text makes a case sensitive search, that is one the
includes the same capital letter and lowers case letter that you specify.
Typing text makes a case-insensitive search for the text string.

        At the screen bottom of the more screen is a message saying More
and a percentage (e.g. - More (65%) - ), which tells you what percentage of
the file you've viewed. At the end of the file, the message - End of File -
is displayed.


